# Journey

Journey is a web service used as the primary content source for Project Magnet

# Journey API Root [/]

This offers the resources available to this API in the form of links in the
JSON body.

## Retrieve the entry point [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "userUrl": "/user",
            "storyUrl": "/story"
        }

# Group Story

Resource related to stories in the system.  A story belongs to a publisher and can be consumed by anyone.

## Story [/story/{storyId}]



+ Attributes (StoryObject)

+ Parameters

    + storyId: 12394dci (number, required)

### View a Story [GET]

+ response 200



# Group User

Resource related to users in the system. A user is both a publisher and a consumer of content.

## User [/user/{userName}]

A User object has the following attributes:

+ Model (application/json)

                + name (string, required)
                + shortBio (string, required)
                + imageUrl (string, required)
                + url (string, required)
                + story (array[Story], required)

+ Parameters

    + userName: KFAStreetArt (required, string) - Unique username of the requested user.

### View a User's information [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "name": "Kinda Fine Street Art",
            "shortBio": "A fine curator of the non-fine arts",
            "imageUrl": "https://media.tengam.org/image.jpg",
            "url": "/user/1",
